[The generated-classpath file has a meaning for running testcases in the current project. If downstream projects want to leverage that file, they have create it in their project (i.e. oozie-core creates one to be able to use MiniMR).

Having the generated-classpath file bundled in the JAR is pointless, and as MAPREDUCE-4082 stated, pollutes the classpath big time.

An alternate way to achieve not having the generated-classpath file in the JAR is to excluded it in the maven-jar-plugin.
, the tools (streaming & archives) failing testcases are passing again.

